reviewText: Course totally lacks enthousiasm. A lot of repetition from the yellow belt course. No in-depth questions about process capability and statistics calculations. No involvement of teachers in the forums. Some sheets and questions are plain wrong (e.g. on cpk calculation). Some presentations are made with a totally unrelated movie as a background, which greatly distracts from the information. I am disappointed, but will finish the specialization. Anyway it is a good motivation to read the handbook.
I found the course is too mechanically taught with slide readings.Needed to focus more on case studies or explaining the significance of formulae

For the most part, this course maintained the same level of competency as the previous courses in the certification. However, the last few modules really phoned it in with just verbatim reading from the course textbook and not going into any sufficient explanation to the meaning of what is being taught. Some information, according to consensus on the forums, is incorrect.Given that this is occurring right when the material starting to become very technical, I have strong concerns moving into the next courses.
Some repetitive courses and confusing sequences of chapter modules.
Too much focus on statistics without context of usage.
Wording of quiz problems was extremely confusing.  I knew the material, but got hung up on how the questions were posed.
The formulas need to be elaborated and the 'Why' needs to be simplified for better understanding.
It was good if the module went own to train how to use Minitab etc to perform statistical calculation
There seemed to be a couple of errors between what was on the slide and what the instructor spoke as he read the slide.

I did not see the LSS Define material. No Charter (problem/goal/benefit statements), VOC or SIPOC. The Process mapping was good. There is way more stats than a normal Green Belt needs to apply the DMAIC methodology, to analyze and improve a business process.
